                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="17905268" author="chia7712" created="Thu, 12 Dec 2024 18:49:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;`ProducerRebootstrapTest` has many issues in using kraft.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1. it passes `unclean.leader.election.enable` as server config but it is not configured on controller node. We should append the config to topic in creating topic.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;2. it assumes `topic` is distributed on &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;0, 1&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;. If the order is not correct, the test can&apos;t pass. We should create the topic manually to ensure the distribution.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;3. in kraft mode, the time to trigger unclean election is 5 mins. it is too long to wait. We should configure controller to reduce the number.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Additionally, `ProducerRebootstrapTest` should be rewritten by java and new test infra. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17906257" author="chia7712" created="Tue, 17 Dec 2024 04:36:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;new test infra has some trouble - &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-18274&quot; title=&quot;Failed to restart controller in testing due to closed socket channel&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;KAFKA-18274&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;KAFKA-18274&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-18275&quot; title=&quot;Restarting broker in testing should use the same port&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;KAFKA-18275&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;KAFKA-18275&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; - so in this jira we focus on migrating it to kraft. &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-18276&quot; title=&quot;Migrate ProducerRebootstrapTest to new test infra&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;KAFKA-18276&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;KAFKA-18276&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; will rewrite it by new test infra&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
